AMOS IN TEXAS TOP TWENTY -</B> &quot;The most impressive, intriguing, and
influential Texans of 1996&quot; - that is how <I>Texas Monthly</I> describes
them on the cover of the September issue. And while Chuck Norris occupies the
cover, it is &quot;<B><I>Altruistic Amos</I></B>&quot;, in his now familiar
Moses pose, complete with halo, who stands atop the table of contents page. Now,
